manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Feel the Rush of Ripjaws V Ripjaws V series DDR4 DRAM memory is designed for sleek aesthetics and performance, making it an ideal choice for building a new PC system or for upgrading your system memory.

Experience DDR4 Performance Available in a wide range of frequency options, Ripjaws V series lets you enjoy a computing experience at DDR4 speeds for gaming, video & image editing, rendering, and data processing.
Rigorously Tested The Ripjaws V DDR4 memory series is tested under G.SKILL's rigorous validation process to ensure outstanding quality.

XMP 2.0 Support Just set and go. Programmed with the latest Intel XMP 2.0 profiles, the only thing between you and overclocked performance is a simple BIOS setting. (*Enable the XMP profile in the BIOS to reach up to the rated overclock speed of this memory kit. Maximum memory speed and system stability depends on the capability of the motherboard & CPU. The memory kit will boot at the SPD speed when BIOS settings are at default.)

42mm Module Height Designed with a 42mm module height, the Ripjaws V series memory is ideal for use with large CPU coolers. (*Please check the specifications of your CPU cooler for actual height clearance.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It works flawlessly alongside the older, version 4 (IV), memory
reviews.reviewText: So, I purchased this set of 32GBs for my ASUS Z170 motherboard, which already had a 16GBs kit of the older Dual Channel memory; G.Skill (2 x 8GB) Ripjaws IV Series. Today marks the 1 month of moderate usage.Originally, I wanted to increase the memory because I will be doing a good chunk of HD AVCHD video recording and editing. In addition to this, a few times in the past, this computer locked up into slug mode and/or crashed because it ran out of memory with too many Apps open and too many Chrome tabs active.So, I was uncertain if this newer version (G.Skill Ripjaws V Series) would work with the older IV (4) Series.Once it arrived, I installed it alongside the older memory sticks and it appeared to run flawlessly.With the Amazon guarantee of return within a limited time, I also decided to put these two sticks, and then all 4 sticks together through extensive memory testing; all together it was over 21 hours of continuous multiple tests using both HCi Design's MemTestPro and the popular MemoryTest86.Result: All memory sticks, 48GBs of dual channel, came through with flying colors.I only needed to increase the memory to 32GBs, but, for the price and the uncertainty of not working well with the older series, I went with this kit of 32GBs.Good news! Now I will never run out of memory in this machine.ps: It arrived in extremely fast timing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 32GB RAM with plenty of uses
reviews.reviewText: It's been a few months now and this 32GB RAM has not failed me or given me issues so far. I'm am running this on a Gigabyte Gaming-7 Motherboard with an I7-6700k Processor. The reason for 32GB of RAM is so I can run multiple virtual machines together as well as games which I admit 32GB of RAM is overkill for just games.Overall i have lots of uses for 32GB of RAM so this product has served me greatly.UPDATE: It's 2019 and this RAM is still holding on strong. I am however running out of RAM Usage with VMs, Video Editing, and Chrome Tabs. Looking to upgrade my PC with another pair of 2x16GB Gskill RAM for 64Gb

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars the product itself works as intended but....
reviews.reviewText: so the thing i got works perfectly fine, my computer reads it as 2x 8gb sticks, and it does its ram job. 8gb? don't you mean 16gb? nope, its 2x 8gb sticks that got sent over and i would understand that mistake because they look physically identical, luckily the vendor was nice enough to do a partial refund and I'm giving it a 4 star more for the product not having noticeable differences between the sticks aside from the little stick. so check your sticks both buyers and sellers.
